# Notes
# ─────
# 1. Style Match is exposed as a top-level dashboard nav entry — sits between
#    Dashboard home and "My creations" so it gets discovered before the
#    user pivots to history.
#
# 2. The `badge: "New"` field is consumed by the existing `<NavMain />`
#    component. If your `NavMain` doesn't already support badges, either:
#      a. Add a small terracotta pill renderer to `nav-main.tsx`, or
#      b. Drop the `badge` field for v1 and add it later.
#
# 3. `Wand2` is already in the lucide-react bundle — no new dependency.
#
# 4. /style-match deliberately lives OUTSIDE the /dashboard subtree (no
#    sidebar chrome) so the marketing Navbar wraps it consistently with
#    /best-ai-art-generator. The sidebar entry just navigates there;
